gameStartMessages.message:
Two Ways to Play

1. Pass the phone: After your turn, pass the phone to the next player.
2. Appoint a Host: One player reads all the questions and wildcards.

gameStartMessages.message:
How to Play:

1. Two Ways to Play:
Pass the Phone: After your turn, pass the phone to the next player.
Appoint a Host: One player reads all the questions and wildcards.

2. Levels & Wildcards:
Each level has 15 questions, getting deeper as you go.
Wildcards may require actions or reflections—follow the prompts!

3. Be Prepared:
Keep pen and paper handy for certain wildcards.

Ready to connect, share, and have fun? Let’s play!

gameOverMessage.name: Beyond family
gameOverMessage.subtitle: Bring your family closer with questions that spark laughter, nostalgia, and heartfelt discussions.

gameOverMessage.message: Take a moment to reflect on your favorite memory from today’s game. Share it with the group and explain why it stands out to you.
Create a time capsule with small notes or items representing each family member’s current dreams or achievements. Decide on a date to open it in the future.
Take a family photo together to capture the moment. Discuss what you’d like to remember about this day and the game.
Discuss and decide on a new tradition or activity that you would like to start as a family. Share why it’s meaningful to you.
Each person writes a letter to their future self, describing their current life and what they hope for the future. Seal the letters and set a date to open them together.
Write a short letter to each family member, sharing what you admire about them or a special memory you have with them. Exchange the letters.
Each person performs a short talent or shares a special skill they have. Celebrate and appreciate each other’s unique abilities.
Name a favorite family memory or something you’ve learned about another family member today.
Agree on a fun family challenge or goal to achieve together within the next month.

Pass the Phone: After your turn, pass the phone to the next player.
